SKIN DISEASE, SEVERE - PHILIPPINES: (PANGASINAN)
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 24 Feb 2014
Source: ABS-CBN News [edited]
http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/video/nation/regions/02/24/14/flesh-eating-illness-spreading-pangasinan


Several people have come down with a so far mysterious disease causing whole-body and deep skin lesions, and other clinical manifestations in Pangasinan, Philippines according to ABS-CBN news. Local health officials describe the manifestations as: "vesicular rashes rising from lower extremities to the head."

The local news story published online on Mon 24 Feb 2014 is entitled "flesh-eating illness in Pangasinan" and covers interviews of individuals affected by this illness, and its clinical manifestations. One of the interviewees explains worm-like organisms surfacing from her skin lesions [submitter: unclear if these were due to fly larvae that had laid eggs and hatched within lesions after lesions were already formed]. The skin lesions appear to spread relatively rapidly, according to other interviewees. Doctors have diagnosed affected patients with several different types of diagnoses (including psoriasis and lupus), but the video indicates that these diagnoses do not fully explain the illness.

Does anyone have information about this illness affecting Pangasinan, Philippines?

--
