******
[2]
Date: Tue 25 Feb 2014
Source: ABS-CBN News [edited]
http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/video/nation/regions/02/25/14/no-mysterious-flesh-eating-illness-pangasinan-health-officer


There is no truth to rumors that a so-called flesh-eating illness is spreading in Pangasinan as reported in "Bandila" Monday night, 24 Feb 2014, the provincial health officer Dr Anna Marie de Guzman said in an interview with radio dzMM on Tue 25 Feb 2014.

De Guzman said the 2 patients who were earlier reported to be carrying a flesh-eating disease were diagnosed with leprosy and psoriasis. She said the female patient who was diagnosed with leprosy suffered a hypersensitivity drug reaction after taking her medications, causing infections on her skin. The other male patient, meanwhile, is suffering from psoriasis, which causes peeling and reddish-white scales on the skin.

De Guzman assured us that neither of these 2 diseases is contagious.

